HDMI( High definitoin Multimedia Interface)
        + Video and audio stream
                - All digital , no analog
                ~ 20 meter distance before the connector starts to drop
        + 19-pin (Type A) Connector
                - One of the most common video connector types.
Display Port
        + Digital information sent in packetized form
                - LIke Ethernet adn PCi Express
                - Carries both audio and video
        + Comptatible with HDMI andf DVI
                - Passoive adpater
                        - DisplayPort > HDMI
                        - DisplayPort > DVI
        + Full-size interface may include a lcoking mechanism.
                - Don't pull when unlocking.
DVI ( Digitial Visual Interface)
        + Single and dual link video
                - Single LIink, 3.7 Gbps (1920 x 1200 60 Hz)
                - Dual Link; 7.4 Gbps (2560 x 1600 at 85 hz)
                - No audio support
        + DVI-A 
                - Analog signals
                - backward compatibility with VGA
        + DVI-D 
                - Digitial signals
        + DVI-I
                - Integratred - Digital and analog in the same
                        connector.
VGA(Video Graphic Array)
        + DB-15 connector
                - More accurately called DE-15
        + Blue color
                - PC system design guide
        + Video only
                - No digital
        + Analog signal 
                - No digital 
                - Image degrades after 5 to 10 meters.
USB-C
        + A connector
                - not a protocol
        + many uses for USB-C
                - Power
                - Thundebolt data
                - Displayport video
                - HDMI video (not common)
                - Mobile High-Definition
                - LInk(MHL)

